<br>
The effect of this, obviously, would be to help all lower level casters, without the extreme effects of KEI on low level characters.<br>
<br>
To wit:<br>
<br>
Make Breeze level 8 (from 16)<br>
Make Clarity level 16 (from 29)<br>
Make Clarity II level 44 (from 54)<br>
Make Gift of Pure Thought level 49 (from level 59)<br>
Make KEI level 54 (from level 60)<br>
Make Tranquility level 61 (from level 63)<br>
Leave Voice of Quellious at level 65<br>
<br>
Now, while this doesn't change things as much as, say, KEI at level 20 does, it does improve mana regen quite a bit. A compromise, if you will. The reason people go to KEI vendors at low levels is because it does make such a dramatic difference and they want to cut downtime. I think everyone can agree that, especially with the higher INT/WIS and overall mana pools available today even to non-twinks (check out the gear available via the froglok newbie quests, for instance), long downtime sucks for the whole group. A modest across the board improvement wouldn't be the end of the world, and I think is long overdue. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz_toon.gif" height="104" width="390" alt="stats" border=0></a>
